o pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that people have found; not one that they have dug:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well that is not deep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well that is wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ElKilábeeyeh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well that is cut through rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard and smooth and large stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo- Habeeb, TA:) of the masc. gender; (Msb, TA;) [not fem. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^orN","text_ar":"بِيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] or masc. and fem.: (Fr, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajobaAbN","text_ar":"اَجْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAbN","text_ar":"جِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibabapN","text_ar":"جِبَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well that is dug wherein a grape — vine is planted; like as one is dug for the shoot of a palm — tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAbN","text_ar":"جِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inside of a well, from its bottom to its top, whether cased with stone or the like or not."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juron","text_ar":"جُرْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a well [app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hollowed stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone basin, for water, placed at the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a well: or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hollowed stone placed over the mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for many a well has such a stone, forming a kind of parapet]. (Zeyd Ibn-Kuthweh, TA.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of leathern bag;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mazaAdap of which one part is sewed to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherein they used to prepare the beverage termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, by use, it acquired strength for that purpose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in a trad., forbidding the use of it; and also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majobuwbapN","text_ar":"مَجْبُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spathe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"envelope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the spadix, or flowers, of the palmtree; also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juf~N","text_ar":"جُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former word was unknown to A'Obeyd: both occur, accord. to different readings, in a trad., where it is said that a charm contrived to bewitch Mohammad was put into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~","text_ar":"جُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juf~","text_ar":"جُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to Sh, (TA,) it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inside"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter here app. signifies, as it does in some other instances, the spathe, not the spadix, of a palmtree]; (K, TA;) in like manner as the inside of a well, from its bottom to its top, is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~","text_ar":"جُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAbN","text_ar":"جِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence the well-known prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAbN falaA taEan~a A^aborFA","text_ar":"جِبَابٌ فَلَا تَعَنَّ اَبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[They are merely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"envelopes of the flowers of palm-trees; therefore weary not thyself to effect fecundation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; applied to a man in whom is little or no good; meaning he is like the spathes of the palm-tree in which are no flowers; therefore weary not thyself by attempting to make him good;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taEan~a","text_ar":"لَا تَعَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tataEan~a","text_ar":"لَا تَتَعَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","Msb","Lth","TA","Fr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}